		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">The Outer Limits</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<dl>
<dd><i>For the album by Progressive Metal band Voivod see</i> <a href="/wiki/The_Outer_Limits_(album)" title="The Outer Limits (album)">The Outer Limits (album)</a><i>.</i></dd>
</dl>
<p><i><b>The Outer Limits</b></i> is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Television_series" title="Television series" class="mw-redirect">television series</a>. Similar in style to the earlier <i><a href="/wiki/The_Twilight_Zone_(1959_TV_series)" title="The Twilight Zone (1959 TV series)">The Twilight Zone</a></i>, with more science fiction than fantasy stories, <i>The Outer Limits</i> is an <a href="/wiki/Anthology" title="Anthology">anthology</a> of discrete story episodes, sometimes with a <a href="/wiki/Plot_twist" title="Plot twist">plot twist</a> at the end. The original series was filmed in artistic black &amp; white and ran for two seasons from 1963 to 1965. In 1995, the series was revived on the Showtime network and ran for seven seasons until 2002.</p>
